2ï¸ Concept: Singleton Scope (Default Bean Scope)
ğŸ“Œ Code (SingletonBean.java)
@Component
public class SingletonBean {

    public SingletonBean() {
        System.out.println("Singleton bean created");
    }
}

ğŸ” Explanation

@Component registers this class as a Spring bean.

Spring automatically creates only one object of this bean when the container starts.

Calling getBean() multiple times returns the same instance.

ğŸ¯ What You Learn

âœ” Singleton is the default scope in Spring
âœ” Only one object is created for the entire application

3ï¸ Concept: Prototype Scope (New Object Each Time)
ğŸ“Œ Code (PrototypeBean.java)
@Component
@Scope("prototype")
public class PrototypeBean {

    public PrototypeBean() {
        System.out.println("Prototype bean created");
    }
}

ğŸ” Explanation

@Scope("prototype") â†’ Tells Spring to create a new object every time getBean() is called.

Spring does NOT create prototype beans at startup.
Bean is created only when you call getBean().

ğŸ¯ What You Learn

âœ” Prototype scope creates a fresh object every request
âœ” Useful for stateful objects or multi-user temporary objects

4ï¸ Concept: Testing Scope Behaviour
ğŸ“Œ Code (MainApp.java)
ApplicationContext context = 
        new AnnotationConfigApplicationContext(AppConfig.class);

System.out.println("-------Singleton Test------------");
SingletonBean s1 = context.getBean(SingletonBean.class);
SingletonBean s2 = context.getBean(SingletonBean.class);
System.out.println(s1 == s2);   // true

System.out.println("-------Prototype Test------------");
PrototypeBean p1 = context.getBean(PrototypeBean.class);
PrototypeBean p2 = context.getBean(PrototypeBean.class);
System.out.println(p1 == p2);   // false

ğŸ” Explanation
ğŸ”µ Singleton Test

Spring creates one object.

Both s1 and s2 point to same memory address â†’ true.

ğŸ”µ Prototype Test

Spring creates new object each time.

p1 and p2 have different memory addresses â†’ false.

ğŸ¯ What You Learn

âœ” Practical behavior of bean scopes
âœ” How to verify object identity using ==